[thinking] **Analyzing Testing Frameworks**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I think it’s better to avoid AssertJ because of the test assertion choices. The existing build uses it, but if the driver applies deterministic dependencies before generation, the generator might write AssertJ into tests, which the normal scaffold might not include. In the repo, many generated tests add it, but if deterministic_setup is omitted, the agent can include it as needed. Also, I don't think commons-logging is necessary with Spring 7, as it pulls spring-jcl instead.
[thinking] 
