 in tests rely on ApplicationContext, RuntimeHints, etc. However, the spring-test POM only brings in spring-core and makes context optional. I should also consider including JUnit since spring-test exposes JUnit4 runner classes, and existing coverage imports org.junit.runner, which would be important if the tests utilize JUnit4 support. But the entries in deterministic_setup are deterministic, not conditional.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"spring-test 7.0.0 publishes only spring-core as a required dependency, but meaningful TestContext/AOT and JUnit 4 runner coverage depends on optional libraries used by Spring Test's normal APIs and existing coverage.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework:spring-context:7.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Spring TestContext and AOT coverage uses ApplicationContext, GenericApplicationContext, @ContextConfiguration, runtime hints, and related context classes; spring-test declares these as optional rather than pulling spring-context transitively.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"junit:junit:4.13.2\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"spring-test still exposes JUnit 4 integration such as SpringJUnit4ClassRunner, and existing coverage exercises that API.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or environment/system property appears required. Prefer in-memory Spring contexts and local test resources. If exercising AOT TestContext processing, use a minimal @ContextConfiguration/GenericApplicationContext setup and do not enable Spring AOT runtime mode unless intentionally testing that path.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"spring-test has many optional integrations, including servlet, MockMvc, WebFlux, JSONPath, Mockito, TestNG, and AssertJ; the listed setup is intentionally minimal for existing meaningful TestContext/JUnit coverage, not exhaustive integration coverage.\",\n    \"The reported failing AOT resource-hint assertion may be a Spring 7 behavior/API change rather than a missing setup problem; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d923795c67b8243016a2929e2b7c481948cb70c77069efafd\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1027, "output": 1391, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28530, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781082566089, "responseId": "resp_0d923795c67b8243016a2929c68ce88194b4374d677b59c968"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing Testing Frameworks**\n\nI think it’s better to avoid AssertJ because of the test assertion choices. The existing build uses it, but if the driver applies deterministic dependencies before generation, the generator might write AssertJ into tests, which the normal scaffold might not include. In the repo, many generated tests add it, but if deterministic_setup is omitted, the agent can include it as needed. Also, I don't think commons-logging is necessary with Spring 7, as it pulls spring-jcl instead.\n\n**Evaluating Spring Dependencies**\n\nI could suggest including the dependency `org.springframework:spring-context:7.0.0`. The rationale is that the Spring TestContext and AOT APIs used in tests rely on ApplicationContext, RuntimeHints, etc. However, the spring-test POM only brings in spring-core and makes context optional. I should also consider including JUnit since spring-test exposes JUnit4 runner classes, and existing coverage imports org.junit.runner, which would be important if the tests utilize JUnit4 support. But the entries in deterministic_setup are deterministic, not conditional.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d923795c67b8243016a2929c78a488194a094b0de127937b6\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKSniCDw5H3ztnx37loqWNv3TwPx7svhh5Eni6FmwsG1FZbTjtOAcn2J3BajjZ_4g-0Jffvv_EgEnIOUA-UcIwoIZBePAUSTPDesF7povRc3XdsdNgnhdZFEjvPHomu4o7VxAy8H6tpsd3d2dVJmlaGKqsV8ZCsQKr0yAWnJX2mE5TNTAel9Mw2PahazVsGi3tDP5H8-hviT2FEiVPcvVUDnwdl7JEh-1iS2CrDwK7cgsjF7V_MVMltrVmpvcfNAzznX8Iv3Z-Pb42uH-ClWUSjAToL1lUrpaTTBBw29Nn89b4TyPjslzV-lPF6_NrMbq6P-H2zhA123Zeq0dyeyApy-uGCK11d9Wk1LNNjBx6v73AVQVEmM0goC0wsbonIB5yl_Cyc3GdQtpOGrRM_xe2ydf6Km4oVcAkVjHX6STjzVHLUAUwYNvKeoyFhc578IILULb2_gXGqjW0EJ67jajBDHaA-svI8f9N1e-IIpBoXhBxMgteq0krMbTzgOfNiIckSqogKwEZ7cfJSTAaS76UPjctod03mPODjBh31lbteR8y9Tr5iLkoE_jKv6jVelcgPdqbbG_ZHcO8QAaN8JEsh4JJ8CJGAL_REAn89P